    "Infectious": {
      "text": "Encephalitis\nMental status changes - personality/behavior changes\nUnlikely to have\nfevers\n, meningismus\nHigh risk: same for meningitis, live near water\nMeningitis\nUsually other etiology for altered mental status, but if negative workup do LP\nConsider\nAmpicillin\nfor\nlisteria\nConsider\nacyclovir\nfor\nHSV\nHigh risk:\nHIV\n,\nDM\n, malignancy, s/p\nceftriaxone\n, prior neurosurgery,\nalcoholism\n, recent\nsinusitis\nPneumonia\nFalse negative\nCXR\n~15-20%\nHigh morbidity\nUTI\nVery common etiology for altered mental status in elderly\nStraight cath\nUA\nResistant organisms likely, look up old urine culture + sensitivity\nHigh risk: pelvic relaxation, indwelling foley >2wks (check for one!), BPH, history prostate cancer\nCholecystitis\nMay not have\nRUQ pain\nor GI symptoms\nAsk about history of gallstones/\nUS RUQ\nSkin/Soft Tissue\nCompletely undress to examine\nOften\ndecubitus ulcers\npresent\nOld photos helpful\nConsider fistula,\nosteomyelitis\n,\nnecrotizing fasciitis",
